ON TUESDAY EVENING LOW CENTRES WILL BE POSITIONED ICELAND AND E OF IBERIA
WITH CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS DOMINATED BY A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING
NE FM CONTINENTAL EUROPE ACROSS THE UK N SEA AND SCANDINAVIA. THROUGH WEDNESDAY
LOW CENTRE DEEPENS S OF PORTUGAL WHILST HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE DEVELOPS IN
THE N SEA. THIS CENTRE DRIFTS E ACROSS INTO THE UK THURSDAY BUT CONTINUES
TO DOMINATE CONDITIONS ACROSS ALL SEA AREAS WITH LOW PRESSURE CENTRE NEAR
IBERIA SINKING S. FURTHER LOW CENTRE ALSO MOVS NE ACROSS ICELAND. HIGH PRESSURE
PERSISTS FRIDAY WITH CENTRE DEVELOPING IRELAND AS THE ANTICYCLONE RIDGES
N AND E. LOW CENTRES REMAIN TO THE N W AND S OF THE ANTICYCLONE AND OUTSIDE
OF THE UK'S SURROUNDING WATERS. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS CULLERCOATS
